EFLNs are a extremely underrated part of Tinker's construct. They are balls that when thrown, will create an explosion on impact. All blocks that are affected by the explosion will drop as items, making them great for mining.

With your newfound plate presser, you can now craft logic cables, and get into Practical Logistics 2!

Practical Logistics allows you to easily see and display the contents of various containers, ranging from chests to fluid tanks. The are somewhat like the RFtools screen's Inventory feature, but better.

As you go through this pack, more functions of Practical Logistics will become available as well.
Used in the creation of mana pools, as well as other items.

Created by dropping certain items (refer to the Lexica Botania) into a pool of mana. 

Used in crafting recipes.

Arcane Archives is a storage mod with a focus on magic, built for the early to midgame.

Even if you are not interested in remote item accessing and storage, there are some items that are worth checking out, such as the Radiant Chest, which a 54 slot chest with a 256 stack size, and the Radiant Trove, which can hold up to 1024 stacks of a single item.

Mana Lens are items that can be applied to Mana Spreaders, and effect how the function.

From damaging mobs, to breaking blocks, to being affected by gravity, these lens are rather versatile.

... Plates! 

Plates will be used to craft a large varity of items, such as machine hulls.

In this pack, breaking a ore block with a mana burst with a bore lens will cause it to split into 2 dust, which can then be smelted into ingots.

Note that mana bursts with bore lens  will pirce blocks, so you can line up a few ores to be split at once.

With you new plates, and other resources, you can now craft a mana fluxfield!

Mana fluxfields allow you to turn Botania mana into redstone flux, allowing you to start crafting (and using) some machines!

Don't worry however, Botania isnt going to become irreverent just because machines are now in play.
